---
title: Warm Pear, Bacon & Mixed Greens Salad with Toasted Walnut Panko, Parmesan & Dijon Vinaigrette
description: This main course salad packed with textures and complementary flavors is destined to become a regular on your table! You’ll toss a bright mix of fresh greens, tender juicy pear, and smoky, crispy bacon with a tangy homemade mustard vinaigrette for bright contrast. Shower your salad with walnut-panko topping and Parmesan for a crunchy, savory finish.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66a7d120b9d3dca06061209b-30bd8ccc.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66aaa884915008628f4468f1-en-US.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 25 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 13 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 780 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/warm-pear-bacon-mixed-greens-salad-66aaa884915008628f4468f1
servings: 2
---

Heat a #medium dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

Carefully discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat from pan.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @pear{1}; thinly slice.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings use 4 TBSP olive oil and 1 tsp sugar.

Heat pan with reserved bacon fat over medium-low heat. (TIP: If pan seems dry, add a drizzle of oil.) Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @walnuts{1/2%oz}, @dried thyme{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

> Be sure to measure the thyme—we sent more!

> Use 1/2 tsp thyme for 4 servings.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{4%oz} and pear with as much vinaigrette as you like.

Divide between shallow #bowls{} and top with @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, bacon, and panko topping. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.